[start section id="$final"]
Final Diagnosis
A.  Sigmoid, rectum, and anus, abdominal perineal resection:  Invasive moderately differentiated (grade 3 of 4) adenocarcinoma, forming a 3.1 x 2.8 x 1.5 cm ulcerative and exophytic mass in the rectum.  The tumor invades through the muscularis propria into the pericolic fat.  Lymphatic/vascular invasion is absent.  The surgical resection margins, including the radial margin, are negative for tumor.  Multiple (13) lymph nodes are negative for tumor.

With available surgical materials, [AJCC ypT3N0](7th edition, 2010).



[end section id="$final"]
[start section id="$gross"]

Gross Description
A.  Received fresh labeled ""sigmoid, rectum and anus"" is an abdominal perineal resection specimen consisting of 31.0 cm in length portion of rectosigmoid colon with a 3.9 x 2.3 cm portion of anus.  The radial margin is inked.  A 3.1 x 2.8 x 1.5 cm ulcerative exophytic mass is present within the rectum, 0.8 cm from the dentate line, 4.1 cm from the anal mucosal margin, and 1.0 cm from the radial margin.  Grossly, the mass extends into the pericolonic fat.  Multiple lymph nodes are identified within the perirectal fat. Representative sections are submitted.  Grossed by GORMAN.



Frozen Sect-Intraop
A.  Sigmoid, rectum, and anus, abdominal perineal resection:  Invasive carcinoma.  Margins are negative.  Hold to assess lymph nodes on permanent sections.

Frozen section histologic interpretation performed by:  Cody T. Nichols, M.D.





[end section id="$gross"]